
[1]responsible

   RESPONS'IBLE, a. [from L. responsus, respondeo.]

   1. Liable to account; accountable; answerable; as for a trust reposed,
   or for a debt. We are all responsible for the talents entrusted to us
   by our Creator. A guardian is responsible for the faithful discharge of
   his duty to his ward. The surety is responsible for the debt of his
   principal.

   2. Able to discharge an obligation; or having estate adequate to the
   payment of a debt. In taking bail, the officer will ascertain whether
   the proposed surety is a responsible man.
